 Butterworth police have appealed to the public to help them identify the body of a man, who was hit by a car in the area. According to police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha, the incident happened on the 21st of February, at about 20:00, along N2 road near Ndabakazi Village, Butterworth. "The deceased is believed to be mentally challenged. He is also believed to be 30 years old," Captain Manatha added. "Anyone who is looking for his/her relative of that description should please contact Butterworth Police at 047 401 1100." 